  "description": [
    "L l o id Party Tactics and Things The following article on left wing tactics by Louis Fraina is reprinted from The Revolutionary Age of which Fraina is editor LEFT WING AND REVOLUTION The distinguishing feature of the Controversy in the Socialist party be tween the right wing and the left wing between the moderates and the revolutionists is that the right wing refuses to develop and defend its real program This is partly fear partly camouflage and partly sheer stupidity The moderates have a program and a consistent program It consists of parliamentarism of reforming capi talism out of existence of municipal izaton and nationalization of industry on the basis of the bourgeoise parlia mentary state of the theory that the coming Socialism is the concern of all classesin short the policy of the moderates which is in itself consist ent while inconsistent with funda mental Socialism is a policy of petit bourgeois liberal state capitalism HOLD POLICY FAILURE But this policy broke down mis erably under the test of the great crisis of imperialism it broke down under the test of the proletarian revolution and revealed itself fundamentally counterrevolutionary But the mod erates essentially still cling to this"
  ],
